From: Abel Vesa <abel.vesa@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Dec 2025 12:45:20 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 346/382] dt-bindings: watchdog: Document X1E80100 compatible

Document the compatible for the X1E80100 platform to the Qualcomm watchdog
binding. The HW implementation is compatible with the KPSS WDT.

Acked-by: Rob Herring (Arm) <robh@kernel.org>
Reviewed-by: Guenter Roeck <linux@roeck-us.net>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20251224-arm64-dts-qcom-x1e80100-el2-add-apss-wdt-v3-1-1801c55d2883@oss.qualcomm.com
Signed-off-by: Abel Vesa <abel.vesa@oss.qualcomm.com>
---
 Documentation/devicetree/bindings/watchdog/qcom-wdt.yaml | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/watchdog/qcom-wdt.yaml b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/watchdog/qcom-wdt.yaml
index 54f5311ed016..f2c4bc900e5f 100644
--- a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/watchdog/qcom-wdt.yaml
+++ b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/watchdog/qcom-wdt.yaml
@@ -43,6 +43,7 @@ properties:
               - qcom,apss-wdt-sm6350
               - qcom,apss-wdt-sm8150
               - qcom,apss-wdt-sm8250
+              - qcom,apss-wdt-x1e80100
           - const: qcom,kpss-wdt
       - const: qcom,kpss-wdt
         deprecated: true
